This paper deals with online learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on the online bandit setting, which is a subfield of reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves game theory concepts, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves algorithms and techniques for analyzing their performance, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
